                <msContents>
                        <summary>A paper manuscript in Telugu script in the Chandra Shum Shere
                            collection at the Bodleian Libraries. It was bought, as part of a
                            private collection of 6330 manuscripts in Benares, by the Maharaja Sir
                            Chandra Shum Shere and presented to the University of Oxford in 1909.
                            The text extends from the beginning of the <title xml:lang="sa"
                                >Jātisamuddeśa</title> to the end of the <title xml:lang="sa"
                                >Kriyāsamuddeśa</title>, although folios 109, 110 and 111 are
                            missing. The manuscript has never been used for an edition and it was not known to Wilhelm
                            Rau, but it is described in Dominik Wujastyk's <title xml:lang="en"
                                >Handlist of the Vyākaraṇa manuscripts in the Chandra Shum Shere
                                Collection preserved in the Bodleian Library</title>. It manuscript
                            was bound into book form by the library, and the folios were numbered by
                            Thomas Gambier-Parry in pencil (Wujastyk 1978, 2). </summary>

